{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UT3kdDArZjHKQcfUc7emcB","type":"tool_result","content":"  1330→\n  1331→- **Sprint is 100% complete.** 74 stories across 17 epics, all done. This is the finish line.\n  1332→- **State repair was fast.** The corruption was identified and fixed in ~2 minutes — the pattern is well-understood by now.\n  1333→- **No regressions.** The state fix was purely metadata — no code changes, no risk of breaking anything.\n  1334→\n  1335→## 5. What Went Wrong\n  1336→\n  1337→- **State corruption recurred for the fifth consecutive session.** The same root cause (story 11-3 reconciliation logic) has been flagged since session 6 and remains unfixed.\n  1338→- **Sprint counters are wrong.** `sprint.done` reads 70 instead of 74. Epic-14 and epic-16 sub-counters are also stale. The derived sprint-status.yaml is correct only because it reads individual story statuses, not the aggregate counter.\n  1339→- **No automated guard.** There is no mechanism to prevent reconciliation from regressing terminal states. The `done` status should be immutable once set — reconciliation should only promote states forward, never demote them.\n  1340→- **Waste compounds.** Five sessions of manual state repair is ~10-15 minutes of pure overhead that could have been avoided with a one-line fix to the reconciliation logic.\n  1341→\n  1342→## 6. Lessons Learned\n  1343→\n  1344→1. **Terminal states must be immutable.** Any state machine that allows `done` to regress to `review` is broken by design. Reconciliation should enforce monotonic forward progression: `pending -> in-progress -> review -> done`. Never backward.\n  1345→2. **Fix infrastructure bugs when they are first found, not on the sixth occurrence.** The state corruption bug was first flagged in session 6. Five sessions later it is still unfixed because it was always cheaper to manually patch than to fix the root cause. That calculus was wrong — cumulative repair cost now exceeds fix cost.\n  1346→3. **Aggregate counters must be derived, not independently maintained.** The `sprint.done` counter drifts from reality because it is incremented/decremented separately from individual story statuses. It should be computed: `count(stories where status == 'done')`.\n  1347→4. **Session issues log should be reset per session.** The current `.session-issues.md` contains entries from session 9 (story 16-8 work). Session 10 added no entries because no work was done. The log should be scoped to a single session or clearly delimited.\n  1348→\n  1349→## 7. Action Items\n  1350→\n  1351→| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n  1352→|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n  1353→| 1 | Fix state reconciliation to treat `done` as terminal/immutable — never regress | CRITICAL | Infrastructure | OPEN (flagged sessions 6-10, five consecutive) |\n  1354→| 2 | Recompute `sprint.done` and epic `storiesDone` counters from actual story statuses | HIGH | Infrastructure | NEW |\n  1355→| 3 | Fix 6 pre-existing BATS test failures | MEDIUM | Tech debt | OPEN (carried forward) |\n  1356→| 4 | Standardize proof document format and provide template to verify subagents | MEDIUM | Process | OPEN (carried forward) |\n  1357→| 5 | Reduce \"unknown\" story cost bucket (18.4% / $114.81 unattributed spend) | LOW | Tooling | OPEN (carried forward) |\n  1358→| 6 | Plan next sprint — all 17 epics complete, project at natural milestone | HIGH | PM | OPEN (carried forward) |\n  1359→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XQb88j2XyoAEyWba8pEnv2","session_id":"9a32080c-76ef-409a-9a0e-138b5be12a95","uuid":"b0c17769-a5c8-49ec-b5b2-cada0ab364c7","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:17:50.717Z"}
